<plot>Meetings. Everybody hates them, but they are absolutely necessary because the competition is right at the doorstep. Four businessmen have the greatest trouble communicating. Yelling all at once is about the only thing they can do and they're not getting an inch closer to their goal: profit. One of the businessmen has an excellent idea. Why not use a wind-up toy dog? Only the one who has the dog may speak. Peace is restored, but not for long.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?575928</url></doc>
